  "notes": [
    "C9 reports runtime network-aware-scheduler behavior; pod placement must be interpreted from captured scheduler, annotation and telemetry evidence rather than from predefined node assignments.",
    "C9 compares DEFAULT, LOADAWARE and NETAWARE variants by logical scenario; comparative claims must preserve the latency profile, traffic profile, tenant count and model mix.",
    "Gateway-routed traffic is the official access path for C9 so Istio-derived deployment traffic annotations can be used as scheduler evidence.",
    "Latency metrics in this report must be interpreted together with the inter-node telemetry matrix and the offered load generated per tenant.",
    "Unsupported or inconclusive scenarios are retained as infrastructure, telemetry, scheduling or capacity-boundary evidence and are not interpreted as measured latency regressions.",
    "cluster-lens placement summaries and signatures are used to interpret response-time results together with scheduler placement evidence.",
    "The C9 report includes latency-profile context and cluster-lens placement tables so response-time results can be interpreted together with the observed scheduler placement."
